{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17608127","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17608127"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T13:29:19+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T13:29:19+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15982"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15982","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15982"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.08,0.4,0.2,0.12,0.2]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8673"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"73458"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8673","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8673"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15982"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"58927"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4932"},{"type":"tags","id":"4935"},{"type":"tags","id":"4949"},{"type":"tags","id":"8576"},{"type":"tags","id":"8597"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"20761"},{"type":"contributions","id":"20764"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"73458","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/73458"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EDuring the second week of human embryonic development, the bilaminar disc forms as cells differentiate into distinct populations. The embryo proper and various extraembryonic tissues develop from specific cell layers.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following structures gives rise to extraembryonic mesoderm during week 2 of development?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Amnioblasts","Epiblast","Hypoblast","Primary yolk sac","Syncytiotrophoblast"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eepiblast\u003C/strong\u003E gives rise to extraembryonic mesoderm through a process similar to gastrulation during week 2 of development. The epiblast is a crucial structure that forms all three germ layers (ectoderm, mesoderm, endoderm) of the embryo proper. It also contributes to extraembryonic tissues including amniotic ectoderm and extraembryonic mesoderm.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAmnioblasts\u003C/strong\u003E develop into the amniotic cavity lining but do not generate extraembryonic mesoderm\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Ehypoblast\u003C/strong\u003E gives rise to the primitive endoderm and contributes to yolk sac formation but does not form mesoderm\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eprimary yolk sac\u003C/strong\u003E develops from the hypoblast and does not generate mesoderm\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Esyncytiotrophoblast\u003C/strong\u003E facilitates implantation and contributes to placental development but does not produce extraembryonic mesoderm\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EUnderstanding the developmental potential of the epiblast is crucial as it is the source of both embryonic and some extraembryonic tissues.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["The epiblast gives rise to extraembryonic mesoderm during week 2 of human development","The epiblast forms all three germ layers (ectoderm, mesoderm, endoderm) of the embryo proper","The epiblast contributes to extraembryonic tissues including amniotic ectoderm and extraembryonic mesoderm"],"references":["Gaillard R, Steegers EA, de Jongste JC, Hofman A, Jaddoe VW. Tracking of fetal growth characteristics during different trimesters and the risks of adverse birth outcomes. Int J Epidemiol. 2014 Aug;43(4):1140-53. doi: 10.1093/ije/dyu036. Epub 2014 Mar 5. PMID: 24603318; PMCID: PMC4258770","Chen X, Liu H, Li Y, Zhang W, Zhou A, Xia W, Xu S. First-trimester fetal size, accelerated growth in utero, and child neurodevelopment in a cohort study. BMC Med. 2024 Apr 29;22(1):181. doi: 10.1186/s12916-024-03390-3. PMID: 38685041; PMCID: PMC11059611","Godfrey KM, Inskip HM, Hanson MA. The long-term effects of prenatal development on growth and metabolism. Semin Reprod Med. 2011 May;29(3):257-65. doi: 10.1055/s-0031-1275518. Epub 2011 Jul 18. PMID: 21769765; PMCID: PMC3685133","Padubidri, V. G., \u0026 Daftary, S. N. (Eds.). (2014). Shaw\u0027s Textbook of Gynecology E-book. Elsevier health sciences","Singh, V. (2022). Textbook of clinical embryology, -E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"58927"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15982"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"58927","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/58927"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-23T21:10:44+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-23T21:11:51+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8673"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"73458"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"